The paper discusses the use of computer vision techniques for plant phenotyping, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on 3D correspondence grouping algorithms, which are commonly used in robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications. The paper also discusses the use of maximum likelihood estimation, which is a common statistical technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and graphics (cs.GR) research.
